{
  "stem": "19923.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 86.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I saw that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "If-- if you want me to talk about Crystal Night?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Yes, please.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Kristallnacht, as you know, happened in November 1938.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Perhaps I should go back and talk a little bit, a month earlier, how my father and Uncle Joe-- Uncle Charles got deported.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- there was some incident that happened, and the Germans used that as an excuse to round up all the Polish nationals living in Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I'm not sure how many there were, anywhere from-- I've heard stories from 15,000 to 25,000 Polish nationals living in Germany, people who had come from Poland after World War I and never became citizens, or were not allowed to be citizens, but were living in Germany.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father had been living in Germany for a number of years.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were given an order by the police to report to the police station within two hours to be deported.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Germans, being efficient people, only wanted the adult males and boys 13 years and older to report to the police station.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They figured if they provided the transportation for the adults, the women and children would follow on their own expense.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father was allowed to take one loaf of bread and, I think, the equivalent of 10 marks, which is about, at that time, was maybe $4, $5, maybe not even that much, to-- with him.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my Uncle Herman also was ordered to be deported.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he still has the order of deportation, which I have now-- [INAUDIBLE] had a copy of that-- that ordered them to report to the police station.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all they were given is two hours.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my older brother was only 10, Joe, accompanied my father to the police station.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
